apps.name: WhatsApp Cloud
apps.description:
WhatsApp Cloud is an app that allows you to seamlessly integrate your WhatsApp conversations with Rocket.Chat, the leading open source chat platform. This integration is made possible through the use of the official WhatsApp Cloud API, ensuring that you can rely on a secure and stable connection between the two platforms.

With WhatsApp Cloud, you can easily access and manage your WhatsApp messages from within Rocket.Chat, without the need to switch between multiple apps. This makes it easy for you to keep track of your WhatsApp conversations and respond to messages quickly and efficiently.

In addition, WhatsApp Cloud integrates seamlessly with other Rocket.Chat features, such as group chat and file sharing, allowing you to collaborate with your team in real-time. As a business, you can use WhatsApp Cloud to serve all of your customers on Rocket.Chat and distribute chats between specialized support agents within your organization.

Try WhatsApp Cloud today and see how it can improve your business communication and customer service with its secure and reliable integration with the official WhatsApp Cloud API!

apps.name: Instagram Direct
apps.description: Omnichannel Integration between Rocket.Chat and Instagram Direct. With the Instagram Direct app, you can handle direct messages from your Instagram contacts directly in Rocket.Chat. It works simply: your customers contact you via Instagram, you answer chats from Rocket.Chat. Some key features of this integration include sending messages with quick reply buttons, welcome messages (starting/closing chat), file sharing, and the correlation between your Instagram accounts and your Omnichannel departments.

en.instagram_handover_protocol_action_descr:
Define the action which should be performed while sending a message to a thread, in order to get access to the thread.

Note: 'Take Thread Control' action will only work if you've configured Rocket.Chat Omni-gateway app as a 'Primary Receiver' from Facebook Apps page settings.
Please find more info about this [here](https://developers.facebook.com/docs/messenger-platform/instagram/features/handover-protocol)
en.instagram_handover_protocol_metadata_des: Define the metadata to be passed along with thread control action request
en.instagram_accepted_media_type_descriptio:
Select the type of files you wish the Agents and your Instagram Contacts can share.

Note: Agents will only be able to share Images due to Instagram API limitations.
en.instagram_auto_delete_messages_upon_dele: Delete messages once it has been "Unsend" from Instagram and Quote replies support

Warning: Before activating this feature, please ensure that you have the following index on "rocketchat_apps_persistence" collection in DB: **appId_1_associations_1**
You'd face performance issues if this index is not present.
This index was added on version 4.2.0, so if you're on or above this version, then you should be good.

Another Warning: If you've selected "Always delete all messages" option, then expect a high storage usage on the aforementioned collection
